      <title>New bard... help!</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=bardtactics&amp;message.id=950#M950</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;I've been reading the various guides and have tried several methods of kiting, but I'm not having much success as a level 30 bard.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;First I tried using my AOEs and kiting the mobs, but I wasn't doing any damage and when I did further research, I found that most of the guides on EQDiva were outdated because the damage doesn't land if the mobs are moving.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Ok, I thought, I'll try the other methods.&amp;nbsp; I then tried chant kiting, using only two mobs that were both dark blue, to try to get the hang of the technique.&amp;nbsp; It took twenty minutes to kill a single mob using my single target DD and DoT.&amp;nbsp; I thought, this is crazy, I could do much better in a group.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;So, I tossed that out the window, too.&amp;nbsp; The third try was with charm kiting.&amp;nbsp; On the same mobs, I was getting resist after resist and my charm was only holding for twelve seconds.&amp;nbsp; Guide after guide says that you should let the mobs beat each other down to about a bubble then chant kite them, but my charm was breaking before they were even halfway.&amp;nbsp; I also couldn't get the charmed mob to re-aggro without letting the other mob hit me, or stopping, targeting the other mob, and sending it to attack.&amp;nbsp; Either way, I was getting beaten on intermittently and often.&amp;nbsp; My regen song didn't do much to restore my HP and I had to stop frequently, approximately every other fight.&amp;nbsp; I can't imagine how this would work with more mobs.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I was fighting mobs in Dulak that were dark blue to yellow in range, with the occasional red.&amp;nbsp; I had temp, and tried variations on my run speed, between SoW and Selos.&amp;nbsp; I also tried it using auto circle, and circling manually.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;My question is, what am I missing?&amp;nbsp; Is there an easier way, or a technique that I've missed somewhere?&amp;nbsp; How on earth can you swarm kite this way, or do I simply need to wait for more powerful songs?&amp;nbsp; At this point, it seems like a *lot* of work and risk for little return.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
